# Web Shell

- `web-app` is an Angular + Nx shell over the KMP web bridge exported from `kmp/bridge-web`.
- Keep browser UI, Angular/Nx setup, and bridge adaptation here.
- Prefer consuming generated bridge types from `libs/src/lib/data-access-kmp-bridge/generated/bridge-types.ts`.
- Prefer `routePath`/generated route table over local route-mapping functions in Angular components.
- If the required shared API is missing, add it either as a pure shared MVI method on the feature component OR as a web-only helper inside `kmp/bridge-web` (pattern-matching/navigation/JSON shims live there, NOT in shared interfaces).
- Ensure bridge lifecycle teardown is wired (`KmpBridgeService.destroy()` on shell destroy).
- Check `web-app/README.md` when working on bridge setup or build integration.
